          <title>Gaetz Ethics report finds &#8216;substantial evidence&#8217; of statutory rape, drug use</title>
          <description><![CDATA[The House Ethics Committee found “substantial evidence” that former Rep. Matt Gaetz (R-Fla.) paid a 17-year-old high school student for sex when he was 35, used illicit drugs like cocaine and ecstasy, and obstructed Congress’s investigation into his conduct.]]></description>
